Couldn't even get it to run. Brand new one plus 8t phone and can't get past the first screen. I press start and the game closes. Looks like a fun game, sure would like to try it.

Apparently collision detection is nonexistent. You can walk through walls, fall through the floor, glitch to all kinds of places you aren't supposed to be able to access. Throw in terrible graphics and make sure the controls are bottom notch too, and that's how you make a 1 star game. Would have given a half star, but could not. Thank goodness I didn't pay for this abomination

Just played the whole game. It was really good. Had some good scare moments. I wish the pop ups for what you can interact with were more obvious. I spent a lot of time in some places because of that, but other than that it was a good experience.

WILL not open. It shows checking license and then it quits.

The game took a long time to download. The terms of agreement was a bit much on the privacy intrusion side. Despite that I accepted the terms and started my first new game. there does not seem to be a tutorial I don't even know what the heck to do. The instructions on how to move are nice but not really a good tutorial. So far the game is bland and uninteresting and I'm tired of wasting my time on it if you collected information from my mobile device delete it now the game is now uninstalled.

Just finished a whole playthrough. Overall this game was really good from start to finish. I enjoyed the creepy vibe it gave off throughout. Not many mobile games have a decent amount of scare to it and this one pulled it off just enough. The only gripe I had was sometimes interacting with items was a bit buggy. Was not a gamebreaker thankfully. Great game and I look forward to more stuff from this team!
